Microprofile Rest-Client with Quarkus 
      MicroProfile REST Client provides a type-safe approach using proxies and annotations to invoke RESTful web services.

We created a project, and inside that project we created APIs. We were calling these APIs from the browser. The browser was sending HTTP requests to our server, and the server was responding. Now suppose you want to call APIs created by someone else inside your project.
    Suppose another team has created an application, and you want to access their APIs from your project. Obviously, your end user will call your project, not the other team’s project directly. But internally, you want to consume their APIs.
     For example, imagine you are building a train reservation application.
You know that you will need train information. But you don’t own the railway database, and you will never get direct access to it. So what do you do?
You call the APIs exposed by the railway system. They must have created APIs that return train data, and you consume those APIs in your application.

