1. none - Hibernate does nothing to the database schema
No table creation, No table update ,No table drop

When to use:
-Production environments
-When schema is managed manually or via Flyway/Liquibase

2. create - Creates database tables if they do not exist, Does NOT drop existing tables

When to use:
- Fresh databases
- Controlled test environments

3. drop - Drops the database schema on application shutdown. Does not recreate tables automatically

When to use:
- Rarely used
- Mostly for experimentation

4. drop-and-create - Drops all existing tables. Recreates the schema at application startup
- All existing data is lost

When to use:
- Local development
- Learning and demos
- First-time schema testing

5. update - Updates the database schema to match entity change
Attempts to add missing columns/tables
Does NOT safely handle complex schema changes


