8. Validation Groups.
Suppose your entity is used in two different places (ie) in one place, the name length should be 10 to 50 characters and in another place, the name length should be 20 to 100 characters

For example:
You have an application where a subscribed user can add up to 2000 songs. But a non-subscribed user is allowed to add only 100 songs. So for such cases, you can create Validation Groups.

-  Create validation group interfaces

public interface BasicNameGroup {}     // name length: 10..50
public interface ExtendedNameGroup {}  // name length: 20..100

