8. Create a interface called MovieMapper which contains the necessary configuration for mapping between the Movie entity and MovieDTO with @Mapper

@Mapper(componentModel = "cdi")
public interface MovieMapper {

	  // --- DAO to DTO, where promotion field is the concatenation of title and director by using expression property
	  @Mapping(target = "promotion", expression = "java(movie.getTitle() + ' ' + movie.getDirector())")
	  MovieDTO toDTO(Movie movie);

	  // -- DTO to DAO, here we not take id into consideration by using ignore property
	  @Mapping(target = "id", ignore = true)
	  Movie toDAO(MovieDTO movieDTO);

}

While mapping from MovieDTO to Movie entity, some fields should not be taken into consideration.
For example fields such as id should not be mapped from the DTO and these values are always managed internally by the Movie entity. Using the MapStruct ignore property, we ensure that such fields are excluded from the mapping process.

Once the configuration is complete, MapStruct automatically generates the implementation of the MovieMapper.

